KW  - Heckscher-Ohlin
KW  - Factor prices
KW  - Technical change
KW  - Factor bias
KW  - Sector bias
AB  - The effects of technical progress on relative factor prices in the two-country, two-good, two-factor Heckscher-Ohlin model are investigated. Technical progress is classified according to factor-augmenting bias, factor-using bias, and sector bias. A complete set of relations between technical progress parameters and relative factor prices, depending on the elasticities of substitution in demand and in production, are worked out. The relative importance of factor bias and sector bias of technical change in determining relative factor prices are examined.
